rations.<br />\nThis release resolves PayPal sandbox issues.<br />\nThis release adds validation to ensure attendee names are entered on the confirmation page.</p>\n<p>Additionally we have added a new shortcode feature for those of you who wish to provide a more robust public attendee list.</p>\n<p><code>[EVR_CUSTOM_ATTENDEE event_id="" custom="" template=""]</code></p>\n<p>To use:<br />\nCreate a page and place the shortcode on a page.<br />\nA. Place the event ID of the event you wish to display attendee list of (must be between &#8220;).<br />\nB. Place the question ID of the question you wish to display the response of. You can display multiple questions, using comma separation, i.e. &#8220;1,2,3&#8243; (must be between &#8220;).<br />\nC. The next variable does not need definition for a default layout, however if you wish to custom layout your listing, you will need to create your custom template.<br />\nD. When using a custom template, place &lt;table&gt;  before the shortcode and &lt;/table&gt; after the shortcode.<br />\nIF you want to use a custom template in the template field, an example would be &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;{ATTENDEES}&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;{QA}&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;  which would display the list of attendees per registrant and any custom questions/responses.</p>\n<p>Tags you can use are:<br />\n{FIRST}, {LAST},{NAME},{ADDRESS},{CITY}, {STATE},{ZIP}, {EMAIL}, {PHONE}, {COUNT}, {TYPE}, {DATE}, {ATTENDEES}, {QA}</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"http://wpeventregister.com/release-6-00-20-now-available/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s: